    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban all non-elite football matches until 2021.",
        "additional_details": "To stop the spread of COVID-19 for an unnecessary exposure risk and protect the NHS from being overwhelmed. \r\nWorkforce\u2019s and Schools are doing a great job of stopping the spread, therefore the crossing over of bubbles for football could be drastic and widespread. Also, it is hard to trace and is heavily reliant on other people.\r\nTo stop the potential of people needing to self-isolate over Christmas. \r\nFootball clubs will be unable to open club rooms, changing rooms or bars.",
        "background": "Ban all non-elite football matches until 2021. Allow teams to create a bubble and train outdoors following COVID-19 procedures through December to regain fitness",
